t-a-way-to-fight-climate-change-180988893/</guid></item><item><title>闪闪发光的金子可以保持几个世纪的光泽。科学家表示他们已经弄清楚为什么贵金属如此不易变色</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/glittering-gold-can-stay-shiny-for-centuries-scientists-say-theyve-figured-out-why-the-precious-metal-is-so-resistant-to-tarnishing-180988881/</link><description>一项研究表明，当金属分裂时，其表面的原子会重新排列成一种非常稳定的模式，不易与空气中的氧气发生反应</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 15:26:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/glittering-gold-can-stay-shiny-for-centuries-scientists-say-theyve-figured-out-why-the-precious-metal-is-so-resistant-to-tarnishing-180988881/</guid></item><item><title>参观 1,700 年前罗马人埋藏的“壮观”的黄金宝石戒指</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-spectacular-gold-and-gemstone-ring-a-roman-likely-buried-for-safekeeping-1700-years-ago-180988891/</link><description>这枚戒指是在英国的一个田野中发现的，被视为“宝藏”，与罗马不列颠的一位军事领导人的夺权行为有关</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 15:03:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-spectacular-gold-and-gemstone-ring-a-roman-likely-buried-for-safekeeping-1700-years-ago-180988891/</guid></item><item><title>这艘二战期间失踪的美国潜艇连同 83 名船员在太平洋被发现</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-american-submarine-USS-Herring-lost-during-WWII-along-with-83-crew-members-has-been-discovered-in-the-pacific-ocean-180988895/</link><description>1944 年，荣获荣誉的美国海军“鲱鱼”号击落日本船只后沉没</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 01:58:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-american-submarine-USS-Herring-lost-during-WWII-along-with-83-crew-members-has-been-discovered-in-the-pacific-ocean-180988895/</guid></item><item><title>刺猬能取代温斯顿丘吉尔吗？看看哪些动物可能很快就会取代英镑上的历史人物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-a-hedgehog-replace-winston-churchill-see-which-animals-may-soon-swap-in-for-historical-figures-on-british-pounds-180988890/</link><description>公众将投票选出蝴蝶、海豚和